cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SI 

The paper investigates the preferences and usage of interfaces by system administrators, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The specific domain of study is firewalls, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves collecting data through an online survey, which is related to networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper provides design recommendations for firewall interfaces, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves understanding the needs and preferences of users.
